The paper discusses the application of dimensionality reduction techniques for cancer classification using microarray datasets. This falls under the domain of machine learning and data analysis, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving classification accuracy using different dimensionality reduction techniques. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these fields also involve machine learning and data analysis. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possibility, as the paper discusses the use of different methods for reducing the dimensionality of data. Finally, cs.BIO (Computational Biology) is a possible sub-category, as the paper deals with cancer classification using genomics data.
